Former Derby County defender Danny Higginbotham says leaving Manchester United for the Rams was the best decision he has ever made. 
 
Higginbotham, who made 86 appearances for Derby before joining Southampton in 2003, has written about his time at Old Trafford in his weekly column for The Sun. 
 
The 38-year-old Sky Sports pundit was first told of Derby&apos;s interest by Sir Alex Ferguson, who told him to consider the offer to join the Rams carefully. 
 
&quot;It was late June 2000, I was 21, living at home with mum and dad and had signed a four-year deal with Manchester United the summer before. Everything was good. Then the phone rang. It was Sir Alex Ferguson,&quot; he said. 
