&quot;It was great to be at a club like United but I was happy to go. It was sink or swim. I had to be brave.&quot; 

 
Derby paid United £2m for Higginbotham and Jim Smith&apos;s side managed to avoid relegation from the Premier League on the penultimate day of the 2000-01 season with a 1-0 victory over United at Old Trafford. 
